The paper discusses a method for estimating defect content and QA effectiveness in software development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The method involves combining expert opinion with measurement data, which could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The case study is conducted in the telecommunication domain, which could be classified under the systems and control (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the statistical performance of the method, which could be classified under programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
